\begin_body

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
7.6.14
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
3.4 
\series default
If 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is an odd integer, then 
\begin_inset Formula $3n+7$
\end_inset

 is an even integer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
3.4 Proof.

\series default
 We assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is indeed an odd integer.
 This means that
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $n=2k+1$
\end_inset

 for some integer 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $3n+7=3\left(2k+1\right)+7=6k+10=2\left(3k+5\right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $3k+5$
\end_inset

 is an integer, 
\begin_inset Formula $3n+7$
\end_inset

 is even.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
3.5.
 
\series default
If 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is an even integer, then 
\begin_inset Formula $-5n-3$
\end_inset

 is an odd integer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
3.5 Proof.

\series default
 
\begin_inset Formula $ $
\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 be even.
 This means that 
\begin_inset Formula $n=2k$
\end_inset

 for some integer 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $-5n-3=-5\left(2k\right)-3=-10k-3=-10k-4+1=2\left(-5k-2\right)+1$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $-5k-2$
\end_inset

 is an integer, 
\begin_inset Formula $-5n-3$
\end_inset

 is an odd integer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
4.5.

\series default
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is an odd integer, then 
\begin_inset Formula $4n^{3}+2n-1$
\end_inset

 is odd.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
4.5 Proof.

\series default
 Assume 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 is an odd integer.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $n=2k+1$
\end_inset

 for some integer 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $4n^{3}+2n-1=4\left(2k+1\right)^{3}+2\left(2k+1\right)-1=4\left(8k^{3}+12k^{2}+6k+1\right)+4k+1$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $=32k^{3}+48k^{2}+28k+5$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $=2\left(16k^{3}+24k^{2}+14k+4\right)+1$
\end_inset


\end_layout

